    "caption": "Climbing rocks, watching for trouble, keeping the troop together.",
    "shortDescription": "Baboons live in complex family groups called troops that can number into the hundreds. They have a strict social order, and every baboon knows its rank — they keep track through grooming sessions that go on for hours. Baboons will mob and harass even large predators when working as a group, sometimes chasing off leopards. Fun fact: Baboons can walk up to twelve kilometers a day searching for food across open grasslands."
